From cou.: 20 The first step in simulating the dynamics is to generate the potential energy surfaces described in Fig. 1. In addition, two-photon transition matrix elements and dynamical Stark shifts are required. State-of-the-art ab initio techniques have been applied to compute the potential energy curves of the magnesium dimer in the Born–Oppenheimer approximation. In all calculations the aug-cc-pVQZ basis set of quadruple zeta quality as the atomic basis for Mg was used. This basis set was augmented by the set of bond functions consisting of [3s3p2d2f1g1h] functions placed in the middle of Mg2 dimer bond.
