From cou.: 44 The photoassociation step is carried out by a two-photon transition from the X1Σ+g electronic ground state to the (1)1Πg excited state. The photoassociation is induced by a femtosecond pulse of 70 fs transform-limited duration, 840 nm central wavelength, and a transform-limited peak intensity of approximately 5 × 1012 W cm−2.
