From Soup: 101 The Hamiltonian is represented on a grid of length R min = 3.0 bohr to R max = 40.0 bohr, with 1024 grid points. The photoassociation is studied numerically by solving the time-dependent Schrödinger equation for the effective Hamiltonian in eqn (9) with a Chebychev propagator. 24,25 We simulate the dynamics with a pulse duration of 100 fs full-width at half-maximum of (FWHM, with respect to the field) for the transform-limited pulse and a central wavelength of 840 nm. Intensity values were calculated in the range of 10 10 W cm −2 to 10 13 W cm −2 , cf. Fig. 2 . This pulse corresponds to the experimental 70 fs pulse (where the FWHM is taken with respect to the intensity profile).
