From cou.: 106 The Hamiltonian is represented on a grid of length Rmin = 3.0 bohr to Rmax = 40.0 bohr, with 1024 grid points. The photoassociation is studied numerically by solving the time-dependent Schrödinger equation for the effective Hamiltonian in eqn (9) with a Chebychev propagator.24,25 We simulate the dynamics with a pulse duration of 100 fs full-width at half-maximum of (FWHM, with respect to the field) for the transform-limited pulse and a central wavelength of 840 nm. Intensity values were calculated in the range of 1010 W cm−2 to 1013 W cm−2, cf.Fig. 2. This pulse corresponds to the experimental 70 fs pulse (where the FWHM is taken with respect to the intensity profile).
From Soup: 106 The coherence measure C e in the excited state allows one to characterize the dynamical contribution to the purity. 26 It is obtained by substracting from e the diagonal elements in the energy representation, squaring and taking the trace. Details of the computational details will be described elsewhere. 16
